      "page": 1,
      "title": "Get An Obama Phone For Free!",
      "article": "<div class=\"article\">\n<h1>Get An Obama Phone For Free!</h1>\n<div class=\"ads ads-detail-one\" id=\"ads1\">\n<div class=\"advertisement\">Advertisement</div>\n<script async=\"\" crossorigin=\"anonymous\" src=\"https://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js?client=ca-pub-2972155632292532\"></script>\n<!-- Phone Ads 1 -->\n<ins class=\"adsbygoogle\" data-ad-client=\"ca-pub-2972155632292532\" data-ad-format=\"auto\" data-ad-slot=\"2576564749\" data-full-width-responsive=\"true\" style=\"display:block\"></ins>\n<script>\n     (adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});\n</script>\n</div>\n<p>The Obama Program is dedicated to redistributing wealth by giving free cell phones to low-income individuals or households. Click through to see how to get one for free!</p>\n<img alt=\"Get An Obama Phone For Free!_1\" class=\"old_img\" data-smallsrc=\"//cdn.uslowcosthousing.com/Images/content_small/get-an-obama-phone-for-free/get-an-obama-phone-for-free_1.jpg\" data-src=\"//cdn.uslowcosthousing.com/Images/content/get-an-obama-phone-for-free/get-an-obama-phone-for-free_1.jpg\" data-webpsmallsrc=\"//cdn.uslowcosthousing.com/Images/content_small/get-an-obama-phone-for-free/get-an-obama-phone-for-free_1.webp\" data-webpsrc=\"//cdn.uslowcosthousing.com/Images/content/get-an-obama-phone-for-free/get-an-obama-phone-for-free_1.webp\" lazyload=\"\" src=\"/Public/Images/load.png\">\n</img></div>"
    },
    {
      "page": 2,
      "title": "Get An Obama Phone For Free!",
      "article": "<div class=\"article\">\n<h1>Get An Obama Phone For Free!</h1>\n<div class=\"ads ads-detail-one\" id=\"ads1\">\n<div class=\"advertisement\">Advertisement</div>\n<script async=\"\" crossorigin=\"anonymous\" src=\"https://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js?client=ca-pub-2972155632292532\"></script>\n<!-- Phone Ads 1 -->\n<ins class=\"adsbygoogle\" data-ad-client=\"ca-pub-2972155632292532\" data-ad-format=\"auto\" data-ad-slot=\"2576564749\" data-full-width-responsive=\"true\" style=\"display:block\"></ins>\n<script>\n     (adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});\n</script>\n</div>\n<h4>1. Is The Government Giving Out Free Cell Phones?</h4>\n<img alt=\"Get An Obama Phone For Free!_2\" class=\"old_img\" data-smallsrc=\"//cdn.uslowcosthousing.com/Images/content_small/get-an-obama-phone-for-free/get-an-obama-phone-for-free_2.jpg\" data-src=\"//cdn.uslowcosthousing.com/Images/content/get-an-obama-phone-for-free/get-an-obama-phone-for-free_2.jpg\" data-webpsmallsrc=\"//cdn.uslowcosthousing.com/Images/content_small/get-an-obama-phone-for-free/get-an-obama-phone-for-free_2.webp\" data-webpsrc=\"//cdn.uslowcosthousing.com/Images/content/get-an-obama-phone-for-free/get-an-obama-phone-for-free_2.webp\" lazyload=\"\" src=\"/Public/Images/load.png\">\n<p>Certainly! Programs like Lifeline Assistance and Lifeline Link-Up provide financial aid for affordable cell phone plans and landline phones. Lifeline Assistance helps pay monthly bills, while Lifeline Link-Up covers phone and installation costs. Government-approved companies offer Lifeline cell phones. </p>\n</img></div>"
    },
    {
      "page": 3,
      "title": "Get An Obama Phone For Free!",
      "article": "<div class=\"article\">\n<h1>Get An Obama Phone For Free!</h1>\n<div class=\"ads ads-detail-one\" id=\"ads1\">\n<div class=\"advertisement\">Advertisement</div>\n<script async=\"\" crossorigin=\"anonymous\" src=\"https://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js?client=ca-pub-2972155632292532\"></script>\n<!-- Phone Ads 1 -->\n<ins class=\"adsbygoogle\" data-ad-client=\"ca-pub-2972155632292532\" data-ad-format=\"auto\" data-ad-slot=\"2576564749\" data-full-width-responsive=\"true\" style=\"display:block\"></ins>\n<script>\n     (adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});\n</script>\n</div>\n<h4>2. Did Obama Start The Free Phones Program?</h4>\n<img alt=\"Get An Obama Phone For Free!_3\" class=\"old_img\" data-smallsrc=\"//cdn.uslowcosthousing.com/Images/content_small/get-an-obama-phone-for-free/get-an-obama-phone-for-free_3.jpg\" data-src=\"//cdn.uslowcosthousing.com/Images/content/get-an-obama-phone-for-free/get-an-obama-phone-for-free_3.jpg\" data-webpsmallsrc=\"//cdn.uslowcosthousing.com/Images/content_small/get-an-obama-phone-for-free/get-an-obama-phone-for-free_3.webp\" data-webpsrc=\"//cdn.uslowcosthousing.com/Images/content/get-an-obama-phone-for-free/get-an-obama-phone-for-free_3.webp\" lazyload=\"\" src=\"/Public/Images/load.png\">\n<p>NO. In fact, it originated in 1996 for landline phones and continues to offer discounts for financially disadvantaged individuals. Link-Up assists with installation and Lifeline Assistance supports monthly bills, with a subsidy of about $10 per month. Presidents Clinton, Bush, Obama, Trump, and Biden have all played a role in its continuation. </p>\n</img></div>"
    },
    {
      "page": 4,
      "title": "Get An Obama Phone For Free!",
      "article": "<div class=\"article\">\n<h1>Get An Obama Phone For Free!</h1>\n<div class=\"ads ads-detail-one\" id=\"ads1\">\n<div class=\"advertisement\">Advertisement</div>\n<script async=\"\" crossorigin=\"anonymous\" src=\"https://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js?client=ca-pub-2972155632292532\"></script>\n<!-- Phone Ads 1 -->\n<ins class=\"adsbygoogle\" data-ad-client=\"ca-pub-2972155632292532\" data-ad-format=\"auto\" data-ad-slot=\"2576564749\" data-full-width-responsive=\"true\" style=\"display:block\"></ins>\n<script>\n     (adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});\n</script>\n</div>\n<h4>3. Who Qualifies?</h4>\n<img alt=\"Get An Obama Phone For Free!_4\" class=\"old_img\" data-smallsrc=\"//cdn.uslowcosthousing.com/Images/content_small/get-an-obama-phone-for-free/get-an-obama-phone-for-free_4.jpg\" data-src=\"//cdn.uslowcosthousing.com/Images/content/get-an-obama-phone-for-free/get-an-obama-phone-for-free_4.jpg\" data-webpsmallsrc=\"//cdn.uslowcosthousing.com/Images/content_small/get-an-obama-phone-for-free/get-an-obama-phone-for-free_4.webp\" data-webpsrc=\"//cdn.uslowcosthousing.com/Images/content/get-an-obama-phone-for-free/get-an-obama-phone-for-free_4.webp\" lazyload=\"\" src=\"/Public/Images/load.png\">\n<p>The eligibility requirements for the free cell phone program have remained unchanged since 1996. Applicants can qualify if their income is at or below 135-150% of the Federal Poverty Guidelines or if they participate in public assistance programs. No changes have been made since President Clinton's administration.</p>\n</img></div>"
    },
    {
      "page": 5,
      "title": "Get An Obama Phone For Free!",
      "article": "<div class=\"article\">\n<h1>Get An Obama Phone For Free!</h1>\n<div class=\"ads ads-detail-one\" id=\"ads1\">\n<div class=\"advertisement\">Advertisement</div>\n<script async=\"\" crossorigin=\"anonymous\" src=\"https://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js?client=ca-pub-2972155632292532\"></script>\n<!-- Phone Ads 1 -->\n<ins class=\"adsbygoogle\" data-ad-client=\"ca-pub-2972155632292532\" data-ad-format=\"auto\" data-ad-slot=\"2576564749\" data-full-width-responsive=\"true\" style=\"display:block\"></ins>\n<script>\n     (adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});\n</script>\n</div>\n<h4>4. Who Pays For The Phones?</h4>\n<img alt=\"Get An Obama Phone For Free!_5\" class=\"old_img\" data-smallsrc=\"//cdn.uslowcosthousing.com/Images/content_small/get-an-obama-phone-for-free/get-an-obama-phone-for-free_5.jpg\" data-src=\"//cdn.uslowcosthousing.com/Images/content/get-an-obama-phone-for-free/get-an-obama-phone-for-free_5.jpg\" data-webpsmallsrc=\"//cdn.uslowcosthousing.com/Images/content_small/get-an-obama-phone-for-free/get-an-obama-phone-for-free_5.webp\" data-webpsrc=\"//cdn.uslowcosthousing.com/Images/content/get-an-obama-phone-for-free/get-an-obama-phone-for-free_5.webp\" lazyload=\"\" src=\"/Public/Images/load.png\">\n<p>There is an ongoing debate about whether phones are paid for by taxpayers. It is subjective as the funds come from a fee on phone bills, known as the Universal Service Fund fee. Both cell phones and landlines are equally subsidized by the government, with landlines often being more costly due to state requirements.</p>\n</img></div>"
    },
